      "id": "step-9-full-picture",
      "title": "The Full Picture",
      "description": "You've now seen the major layers of Overlay: the frontend (routing, components, API routes), the shared library (models, tools, auth, integrations), and the serverless backend (data model, real-time queries, billing). The key data flow is: the user sends a message, the chat interface calls the appropriate API route, which builds a tool set, streams a response from the AI model, executes any tool calls, persists the result, and pushes a real-time update back to the UI.",
